<div id="review_620373259" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/620373259" />
    <a title="Gaele" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9146116-gaele"><img alt="Gaele" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1599408124p2/9146116.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/620373259?book_show_action=true">May 20, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gaele" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gaele" href="/user/show/9146116-gaele">Gaele</a>
      </span>

          added it




        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9146116-gaele?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9146116-gaele?shelf=plagiarism">plagiarism</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer620373259" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12472385349034354426"><br/><strong>*****PLAGIARIST WARNING ****** AS OF 19 FEBRUARY 2019 THIS &apos;AUTHOR&apos; HAS BEEN ACCUSED OF PLAGIARISM - 34 (AND COUNTING) TITLES FROM 26 (AND COUNTING) AUTHORS AS WELL AS 2 NEWS ARTICLES AND 2 RECIPES. I CANNOT VERIFY OR VOUCH THAT ANY OF THIS REVIEW IS BASED ON A NOVEL OF ORIGINAL WORK FROM &apos;STATED AUTHOR&apos; AS HISTORY SUGGESTS OTHERWISE. </strong><br/><br/><br/><s>This was an emotional read, with compelling characters, an interesting mystery and a beautifully descriptive writing style. As a debut offering, Ms. Serruya has pr</s></span>
  <span id="freeText12472385349034354426" style="display:none"><br /><strong>*****PLAGIARIST WARNING ****** AS OF 19 FEBRUARY 2019 THIS 'AUTHOR' HAS BEEN ACCUSED OF PLAGIARISM - 34 (AND COUNTING) TITLES FROM 26 (AND COUNTING) AUTHORS AS WELL AS 2 NEWS ARTICLES AND 2 RECIPES. I CANNOT VERIFY OR VOUCH THAT ANY OF THIS REVIEW IS BASED ON A NOVEL OF ORIGINAL WORK FROM 'STATED AUTHOR' AS HISTORY SUGGESTS OTHERWISE. </strong><br /><br /><br /><s>This was an emotional read, with compelling characters, an interesting mystery and a beautifully descriptive writing style. As a debut offering, Ms. Serruya has produced a fairly competent work, well plotted, paced and fleshed out. While I found some of the description overly focused on the materialistic often to the detriment of the luxe feel that I believe the author was looking to achieve: I did understand the styling and was able to visualize the story as I read. <br /><br />Characters were well defined, if not perfect: their backstories and turbulent pasts all manage to find logical and rational explanations although there were some curiously neglected traits left unexamined: Sophiaâ€™s facility with languages was unexplored, yet mentioned as a badge of honor. Additionally there was some confusion with her behavior and reactions, where she did not react to obviously abusive behaviors from the two men in her life with a similar approach. The relationship dynamic was similar with both Alistair and Ethan, yet their aggression triggered wholly different reactions from her. That inconsistency still niggles at me. <br /><br />While this book is characterized as contemporary erotic- the sexual scenes, while highly erotic in nature are not as frequent as I have come to see, but they are steamily sensual and sexual with well detailed scenes, believable and solid in their crafting. <br /><br />Even with the few issues, this was a highly enjoyable and readable story â€“ one suited for people who like contemporary romance with more emotion and luxurious settings, with a feel of Jacque Collins and less a sense of 50 Shades. </s><br /><br />I received an eBook copy for purpose of honest review for Full Moon Bites tours. I was not compensated for this review: all conclusions are my own responsibility.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12472385349034354426" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


